CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 5, 1961, pg. A28, reads: "In Park Net Tourney - This foursome participated in recent Pittsburgh Public Parks Tennis Tournament at Frick Park Courts. From left, in first rounds Ray Brown defeated Bill Taylor, 6-2, 6-2; Walt Harper defeated Jack Barek, 6-0, 6-0; Billy Colbert, seeded No. 2 in the tourney, defeated John Christian, 6-1, 6-1, and Dan Kean, Gulf Oil Co., was forced to default because of business.  Brown and Harper were eliminated in Monday's play. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Participants in Pittsburgh Public Parks Tennis Tournament, from left: Ray Brown or "Brownie" Wilson, Walt Harper, Bill "Billy" Colbert, and Dan Kean standing in front of tennis court at Frick Park
